data.name: WelcomeDescription.Text
data.value:
This wizard helps you create and configure a new Macintosh or add an existing Macintosh to the Virtual Mac Console.
The Macintosh configuration is stored in a .mcc file.
To continue, click Next.

data.name: DiskInfo.Text
data.value: A Macintosh needs a disk to install the operating system. You can create a new disk to install MacOS (Or Linux) or you can use an exisitng disk with a preinstalled operating system.

data.name: RAMCustomInvalidSize.Text
data.value: Please use a valid size between %n and %x

data.name: CreateNoWizardLabel.Text
data.value: Recommended for more users. Creates a Macintosh in base to the system you want to install on it.

data.name: WelcomeTitle.Text
data.value: Welcome to the New Macintosh Wizard

data.name: HwInfo.Text
data.value: Select the emulator you plan to use. Some emulators run some versions of Mac OS and System Software. Try different emulators to see different versions of Mac OS. Remember that you can customise the hardware shown here, so don't worry if you wanted more memory, more disk or even another CPU (Only available for some emulators).

data.name: MacNameLabel.Text
data.value: Give a name to your Macintosh, remember to make it descirptive, something like "Mac OS 7" or "iMac G3" are good examples.

data.name: CreateNormalLabel.Text
data.value: Recommended for advanced users. Creates a Macintosh guiding you to increase or decrease the resources you assign to this Macintosh.

data.name: AddInfo.Text
data.value: Select the file to add to the Virtual Mac Console

data.name: HwInfoDef.Text
data.value: Recommended hardware for this operating system:

data.name: CreateAddExistLabel.Text
data.value: For Basilisk, SheepShaver and PearPC users. Creates a Macintosh from a file in your physical machine.

data.name: EndInfo.Text
data.value: You have succefully completed the New Macintosh Wizard. Your Macintosh will be created with the following attributes:

data.name: RAMInfo.Text
data.value:
A Macintosh needs memory to boot the system, and the applications need it to run. A more recent system needs more memory, also the heavier apps you want to run, the more memory you will need. It's recommended that you use the recommended memory unless you want to run heavy applications.
The recommended memory is [ %m MB ]

data.name: EndInfoFinish.Text
data.value: To close this wizard and create this Mac, click Finish.

data.name: Description.Text
data.value: You can create a new Mac or add an existing one to the Virtual Mac Console
